## Summary — Total Screens to Build

| Phase | Screens | Priority |
|-------|---------|----------|
| Phase 0 — Foundation | 4 components | 🔴 Critical (build first) |
| Phase 1 — Reporting | 10 screens | 🟡 High |
| Phase 2 — Vendor & Employee | 5 screens | 🟡 High |
| Phase 3 — Customer | 3 screens | 🔴 Critical |
| Phase 4 — Payments | 6 screens | 🔴 Critical |
| Phase 5 — Complaints | 5 screens | 🟡 High |
| Phase 6 — Inventory | 1 screen + 2 modals | 🟢 Medium |
| Phase 7 — Area Zones | 2 screens | 🟢 Medium |
| Phase 8 — Admin | 5 screens | 🟢 Medium |
| Phase 9 — Supporting | 3 screens | 🟡 High |
| **Total** | **~44 screens** | |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Every screen must follow the ISPApp agent skills: use design tokens exclusively (no hardcoded colors), handle 4 states (loading skeleton → error → empty → success), use Zustand for client state + React Query for server state, and follow the clean architecture layer rules.
